      <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--orange);margin-bottom:.75rem;">Our story</div>
      <h1>Built by people who read labels — and got confused</h1>
      <p>SugarWatch started when our founder, realised that Indian food labels were technically compliant but practically useless. That's changing now.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-card"><h3>The mission</h3><p>To give every Indian consumer a simple, honest answer to one question: how much sugar am I actually eating? We translate grams into teaspoons, catch hidden sugars, and build tools that work for Indian diets — not Western ones.</p></div>
      <div class="about-card"><h3>The data</h3><p>Our database combines Open Food Facts, FSSAI public disclosures, and manual verification from our team. Every product is reviewed for accuracy. We flag hidden sugars using a 60-alias detection engine trained on Indian ingredient lists.</p></div>
      <div class="about-card"><h3>Why teaspoons?</h3><p>Grams are abstract. You've never measured 28 grams in your kitchen. But you've spooned sugar into chai. One teaspoon = 4 grams. That's the entire philosophy behind SugarWatch — make it real.</p></div>
      <div class="about-card"><h3>Privacy</h3><p>We don't sell your data. Food logs are stored locally on your device unless you opt into cloud sync. We don't require an account to scan products. No ads, no trackers beyond anonymous analytics.</p></div>
